// 03b-data-thermo-fuel — Thermophysical property and fuel-specific databases

The thermophysical property labels used throughout this work were assembled from six complementary sources that collectively span more than 1.2 million experimental data points across thousands of compounds. These sources differ in accuracy, chemical coverage, and data format, but together they provide sufficient breadth and depth to train machine learning models for viscosity, surface tension, and density prediction. @tbl-thermo-summary presents a consolidated overview of each source, including the number of compounds and data points contributed to the training pipeline.

